title: "Join Us"
---

Women in Cognitive Science – Europe (WiCS-Europe) is an inclusive community dedicated to promoting
equity, diversity, and inclusion (EDI) in cognitive science across Europe and beyond.

There are many ways to get involved — whether you want to stay informed, actively contribute to
our initiatives, or help shape the future of the organization.

---

## Subscribe to our newsletter

Stay up to date with WiCS-Europe activities, including upcoming events, calls for participation,
mentoring opportunities, and other initiatives related to EDI in cognitive science.

Our newsletter is open to people of **all gender identities**, career stages, and disciplines.

### Newsletter subscription 
*(Form coming soon)*
---

## Co-organize an event with WiCS-Europe

WiCS-Europe regularly co-organizes:
- Panel discussions
- Workshops and seminars
- Speed mentoring sessions
- Satellite events at international conferences

If you are organizing (or planning to organize) a conference, workshop, or academic meeting and
would like to collaborate with WiCS-Europe, we would be very happy to hear from you.

Co-organizing with WiCS-Europe can include:
- Joint event branding
- Support with speaker selection and moderation
- Promotion through our communication channels
- Inclusion of mentoring or EDI-focused activities

**Contact us at:**  
**[wics.europe@gmail.com](mailto:wics.europe@gmail.com)**

---

## Everyone is welcome

WiCS-Europe activities and opportunities are open to scientists of **all gender identities**,
career stages, and backgrounds. We strongly encourage participation from individuals belonging to
underrepresented groups in academia.

If you are interested in getting involved or have questions, please don’t hesitate to reach out.

**Contact:**  
**wics.europe@gmail.com**
